urls.description: VHDL designers are generally not spoiled with Verification IP (VIP). In fact, if you are using any sort of verification IP at all, then most likely it was developed in-house with the company you are working for. And most likely, such verification IP is a collection of BFM (Bus Functional Model) procedures which lacks any advanced features of a modern verification framework.
